('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:2ee3b257', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "How do you say ‘I am the third child’?", "options": ["Soy el tercer hijo", "Soy el tercero hijo", "Soy el hijo tercer", "Soy tercer de hijo"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘tercer’ shortens before a masculine singular noun: el tercer hijo (like ‘primer’, ‘buen’)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:fdff52b6', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Aquí tienes mis datos personales: nombre, edad y sexo.’ — what are ‘datos personales’?", "options": ["personal details/data", "personal opinions and beliefs", "personal belongings, like a bag", "a personal diary or journal"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "datos personales = personal details/data (name, age, etc.), not opinions or objects."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:01833117', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Mi amigo Hans es alemán.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. Where is Hans from?", "options": ["Germany", "Italy", "Britain", "China"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "alemán = German. The other options are the other nationalities on this page."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:ce9af27a', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Tengo un recuerdo precioso de mi abuela.’ — what is ‘un recuerdo’?", "options": ["a memory", "a present, a gift", "a photograph, nothing more", "a letter or postcard"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "un recuerdo = a memory (also can mean souvenir), not simply a gift or photo."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:4bf5cb17', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘Chinese’?", "options": ["chino", "chico", "china (the country only)", "checo"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "chino = Chinese. ‘chico’ = boy; ‘checo’ = Czech — classic mix-ups."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:a6167bd6', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Oigo a mi hermano cantar en su cuarto.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What is being said?", "options": ["I can hear my brother singing in his room", "I can see my brother dancing in the garden", "I can hear my sister singing in the kitchen", "I want my brother to stop singing right now"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "oigo = I hear/can hear. Distractors swap the sense verb, the sibling or the place."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:mcq:4d30dfae', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Mi madre siempre me ha dicho que soy parecido a mi abuelo.’ — what does ‘ha dicho’ mean here?", "options": ["has said / has told", "is going to say tomorrow", "used to say a long time ago", "never said anything at all"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘ha dicho’ is the perfect tense of decir (to say/tell) = has said/told."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:74a7e953', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "For age, Spanish uses ‘tener’ — ‘tengo quince años’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "You literally ‘have’ years: tengo… años. ‘Soy… años’ is wrong."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:b2b3db46', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "Hair and eyes use ‘tener’: ‘tengo el pelo rubio’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "Spanish ‘has’ hair and eyes, and keeps the article (el/los)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:e503397e', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘hijo único’ means ‘a unique son’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "It means ‘only child’ — único here = only."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:91656729', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘mis hermanos’ is correct because the possessive agrees with the plural noun."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "mi → mis to match a plural noun (hermanos)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:d50d7fba', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘mayor’ means ‘younger’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "mayor = older; menor = younger."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:356ff3cb', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Tengo los ojos marrón’ is correct."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "Eyes are plural, so the colour must agree: los ojos marrones."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:dfc2869f', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘llevar’ is used for glasses: ‘llevo gafas’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "llevar = to wear (glasses, clothes)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:68a216fc', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "Build/height uses ‘ser’: ‘soy alto’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "ser describes what you are like: soy alto/alta."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:41a09006', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘tercer’ becomes ‘tercero’ before a masculine singular noun."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "It''s the opposite: ‘tercero’ shortens to ‘tercer’ before a masculine singular noun (el tercer hijo)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:96e3aef3', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘madrastra’ means ‘stepmother’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "madrastra = stepmother; padrastro = stepfather."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:tf:2d1ee208', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "Spanish speakers usually only use one surname, never two."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "It''s common to use two surnames — father''s then mother''s, e.g. González Pérez."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:533e17a0', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I introduce myself?", "reading": "<p>The building blocks for talking about yourself — tap 🔊 to hear each one.</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"me llamo\">me llamo…</span></td><td>my name is…</td><td><span data-say=\"tengo catorce años\">tengo… años</span></td><td>I am … years old</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"soy de\">soy de…</span></td><td>I am from…</td><td><span data-say=\"vivo en\">vivo en…</span></td><td>I live in…</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Model: <span data-say=\"Me llamo Ana, tengo quince años y vivo en Madrid.\">Me llamo Ana, tengo quince años y vivo en Madrid.</span></p>\n            <p><strong>Big rule:</strong> for age Spanish uses <strong>tener</strong> (to have), not ‘ser’ — you literally ‘have’ years.</p>", "question": "How do you say ‘I am 15 years old’?", "options": ["Tengo quince años", "Soy quince años", "Estoy quince años", "Tengo quince año"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Age uses tener: ‘tengo quince años’ — never ‘soy’. ‘años’ is plural."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:6995f9f0', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I describe how I look?", "reading": "<p>Use <strong>ser</strong> for build/height and <strong>tener</strong> for hair and eyes:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"soy alto\">soy alto / alta</span></td><td>I am tall</td><td><span data-say=\"soy bajo\">soy bajo / baja</span></td><td>I am short</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"soy delgado\">soy delgado / delgada</span></td><td>I am slim</td><td><span data-say=\"llevo gafas\">llevo gafas</span></td><td>I wear glasses</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Model: <span data-say=\"Soy alta y delgada, y llevo gafas.\">Soy alta y delgada, y llevo gafas.</span> <em>(alt<strong>a</strong>, delgad<strong>a</strong> — female.)</em></p>", "question": "Which verb describes hair and eyes — ‘tengo el pelo…’?", "options": ["tener (to have)", "ser (to be)", "estar (to be)", "llevar (to wear)"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Spanish ‘has’ hair and eyes: tengo el pelo…, tengo los ojos… ‘llevar’ is for glasses/clothes."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:d10d98c1', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I describe my hair and eyes?", "reading": "<p>Use <strong>tengo el pelo…</strong> (I have … hair) and <strong>tengo los ojos…</strong> (I have … eyes). Note the article (‘el’, ‘los’) — Spanish keeps it.</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el pelo rubio\">el pelo rubio</span></td><td>blond hair</td><td><span data-say=\"el pelo moreno\">el pelo moreno</span></td><td>dark hair</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el pelo castaño\">el pelo castaño</span></td><td>brown hair</td><td><span data-say=\"corto o largo\">corto / largo</span></td><td>short / long</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"los ojos azules\">los ojos azules</span></td><td>blue eyes</td><td><span data-say=\"los ojos marrones\">los ojos marrones</span></td><td>brown eyes</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Colours agree: eyes are plural, so <span data-say=\"Tengo los ojos verdes.\">Tengo los ojos verdes.</span></p>", "question": "How do you say ‘I have long hair’?", "options": ["Tengo el pelo largo", "Llevo el pelo largo casi siempre", "Soy el pelo largo", "Tengo el pelo larga"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Hair uses tener + the article ‘el’; ‘pelo’ is masculine so the colour/length agrees: largo (not larga)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:6f0a12a8', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Who is in my family?", "reading": "<p>Family members (<strong>la familia</strong>):</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"los padres\">los padres</span></td><td>parents</td><td><span data-say=\"los abuelos\">los abuelos</span></td><td>grandparents</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el hermano mayor\">el hermano mayor</span></td><td>older brother</td><td><span data-say=\"la hermana menor\">la hermana menor</span></td><td>younger sister</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el tío\">el tío / la tía</span></td><td>uncle / aunt</td><td><span data-say=\"el primo\">el primo / la prima</span></td><td>cousin</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p><span data-say=\"Soy hijo único.\">Soy hijo único.</span> = I’m an only child. <span data-say=\"En mi familia hay cuatro personas.\">En mi familia hay cuatro personas.</span></p>\n            <p><span data-say=\"Mis primos forman parte de mi familia numerosa.\">Mis primos forman parte de mi familia numerosa.</span> = My cousins are part of my large family. <span data-say=\"A veces oigo a mi hermano cantar en su cuarto.\">A veces oigo a mi hermano cantar en su cuarto.</span> = Sometimes I hear my brother singing in his room. <span data-say=\"Recibo muchos mensajes de mi familia cuando viajo.\">Recibo muchos mensajes de mi familia cuando viajo.</span> = I receive lots of messages from my family when I travel.</p>", "question": "What does ‘mi hermana menor’ mean?", "options": ["my younger sister", "my older sister", "my younger brother", "my cousin"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "hermana = sister; menor = younger. mayor = older."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:fc1625a0', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I say ‘my’ and ‘your’? (possessives)", "reading": "<p>Possessive adjectives agree with the <strong>number</strong> of the thing owned (one or many), NOT with you:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"mi hermano\">mi</span> (one thing)</td><td>my — <span data-say=\"mi hermano\">mi hermano</span></td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"mis hermanos\">mis</span> (more than one)</td><td>my — <span data-say=\"mis hermanos\">mis hermanos</span></td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"tu casa\">tu / tus</span></td><td>your — tu casa, tus amigos</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"su perro\">su / sus</span></td><td>his / her / their</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>So it’s <strong>mi</strong> hermano but <strong>mis</strong> hermanos — the ‑s matches the plural noun.</p>", "question": "How do you say ‘my brothers’ (more than one)?", "options": ["mis hermanos", "mi hermanos", "mío hermanos", "mis hermano"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The possessive agrees with the plural noun: mis hermanos."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:92d900cc', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Higher: longer, richer descriptions", "reading": "<p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> Add quantifiers and join clauses to describe more precisely:</p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>Quantifiers: <span data-say=\"bastante alto\">bastante alto</span> (quite tall), <span data-say=\"un poco tímido\">un poco tímido</span> (a bit shy). <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li>Relative ‘que’: <span data-say=\"Tengo un hermano que se llama Luis.\">Tengo un hermano que se llama Luis.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li>Combine appearance + who: <span data-say=\"Mi hermana mayor, que es muy alta, tiene el pelo largo y rizado.\">Mi hermana mayor, que es muy alta, tiene el pelo largo y rizado.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n              <li>Perfect tense (‘has/have’): <span data-say=\"Mi madre siempre me ha dicho que soy parecido a mi abuelo.\">Mi madre siempre me ha dicho que soy parecido a mi abuelo.</span> — My mother has always told me I look like my grandfather. <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span></li>\n            </ul>", "question": "‘Tengo un hermano que se llama Luis’ — what does ‘que’ do here?", "options": ["it links two ideas (‘who’ / ‘that’)", "it is used to ask a question meaning ‘what?’", "it means ‘because’", "it makes the sentence a plan"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Relative ‘que’ = who/that; it joins ‘I have a brother’ + ‘he is called Luis’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:de46cf3b', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Who else is in my family? Stepfamily, ages and names", "reading": "<p>Family isn''t just parents and siblings — here''s more people, and how Spanish names work:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"la madrastra\">la madrastra</span></td><td>stepmother</td><td><span data-say=\"el padrastro\">el padrastro</span></td><td>stepfather</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"mamá\">mamá</span></td><td>mum (informal)</td><td><span data-say=\"papá\">papá</span></td><td>dad (informal)</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"una niña\">una niña</span></td><td>a (young) girl</td><td><span data-say=\"un bebé\">un bebé</span></td><td>a baby</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"un anciano\">un anciano</span></td><td>an elderly man</td><td><span data-say=\"un adulto\">un adulto</span></td><td>an adult</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el nacimiento\">el nacimiento</span></td><td>birth</td><td><span data-say=\"el apellido\">el apellido</span></td><td>surname</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Spanish speakers often use <strong>two</strong> surnames — father''s then mother''s: <span data-say=\"Mi apellido es González Pérez.\">Mi apellido es González Pérez.</span> And to say ‘the youngest’ of a group, use <span data-say=\"el menor\">el menor / la menor</span>: <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> <span data-say=\"Soy la menor de mis hermanos.\">Soy la menor de mis hermanos.</span></p>", "question": "What does ‘mi padrastro’ mean?", "options": ["my stepfather", "my stepmother", "my grandfather", "my father-in-law, my wife''s dad"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "padrastro = stepfather; madrastra = stepmother."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:learn:5f4d921e', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Where is my family from? Nationalities and more appearance", "reading": "<p>Nationality adjectives change for a female (add ‑a) — note the accent often disappears:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"europeo\">europeo / europea</span></td><td>European</td><td><span data-say=\"alemán\">alemán / alemana</span></td><td>German</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"italiano\">italiano / italiana</span></td><td>Italian</td><td><span data-say=\"británico\">británico / británica</span></td><td>British</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"chino\">chino / china</span></td><td>Chinese</td><td><span data-say=\"blanco\">blanco / blanca</span></td><td>white</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>More words for describing people:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el pelo gris\">el pelo gris</span></td><td>grey hair</td><td><span data-say=\"un poco gordo\">un poco gordo / gorda</span></td><td>a bit overweight</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"hermoso\">hermoso / hermosa</span></td><td>beautiful</td><td><span data-say=\"precioso\">precioso / preciosa</span></td><td>beautiful, gorgeous</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"un tatuaje\">un tatuaje</span></td><td>a tattoo</td><td><span data-say=\"parecerse a\">parecerse a</span></td><td>to look like, resemble</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Family resemblance: <span data-say=\"Me parezco mucho a mi madre; somos muy semejantes.\">Me parezco mucho a mi madre; somos muy semejantes.</span> = I look a lot like my mother; we are very similar. Forms often ask your <span data-say=\"sexo\">sexo</span> (sex/gender) as well as your name and age.</p>\n            <p><span data-say=\"Puedo identificar a mi padre en cualquier foto por su pelo moreno.\">Puedo identificar a mi padre en cualquier foto por su pelo moreno.</span> = I can identify my father in any photo by his dark hair. <span data-say=\"Me sorprende lo mucho que me parezco a mi padre.\">Me sorprende lo mucho que me parezco a mi padre.</span> = It surprises me how much I look like my father. <span data-say=\"Le agradezco a mi abuela cada recuerdo que tengo.\">Le agradezco a mi abuela cada recuerdo que tengo.</span> = I''m grateful to my grandmother for every memory I have.</p>", "question": "What does ‘me parezco a mi padre’ mean?", "options": ["I look like my father", "I disagree with my father", "I live apart from my father", "I get on badly with my father, not well at all"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "parecerse a = to look like/resemble. Don''t confuse it with ‘discutir’ (to argue) or ‘llevarse mal’ (get on badly)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends:misc:f87d6ef2', 'spanish', 'spanish:1-1-me-my-family-and-friends', '1.1 Me, My Family and Friends', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Soy quince años.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Tengo quince años.</p>", "question": "Why ‘Tengo quince años’, not ‘Soy…’?", "options": ["Spanish expresses age with ‘tener’ (to have)", "‘ser’ can only ever be used with jobs", "you must put the number after the verb ‘ser’", "age always needs the verb ‘estar’ instead"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "In Spanish you ‘have’ years: tengo… años."}'::jsonb),
